  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d01fd2d64a9249049aaa77d5c12a82fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: Question9
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: Why do we insert a cotton plug into the stem of the inverted funnel?
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: The cotton plug used to seal the stem of the inverted funnel prevents
    the escape of vapours of ammonium chloride obtained during heating. However,
    it may allow some vapours to escape into the atmosphere.
  options:
  - To prevent the escape of vapours formed during heating
  - To absorb the vapours obtained after heating
  - To absorb the vapours obtained after heating
  - None of the above
  correctOptionIndex: 0
